Tibor Racsits, 42, had gone to pick up his daughter Kiara from the movies at Charlestown Square in Newcastle, north of Sydney, on Sunday night when they were attacked .
He was dragged across the road by at least three young men before being kicked in the stomach and head .
His daughter can be heard screaming as she runs to help but she is pushed from behind by a young girl and slams face-first into the concrete .
The father and daughter were treated at the scene for minor injuries .